<Link id="l00030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="30"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A FILO worklist that prioritizes on re-insertion without duplication.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00031" /><CodeLine lineNumber="31"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00032" /><CodeLine lineNumber="32"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This is very similar to a \\c SetVector with the primary difference that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><Highlight kind="comment">/// while re-insertion does not create a duplicate, it does adjust the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><Highlight kind="comment">/// visitation order to respect the last insertion point. This can be useful</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><Highlight kind="comment">/// when the visit order needs to be prioritized based on insertion point</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><Highlight kind="comment">/// without actually having duplicate visits.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Note that this doesn&#39;t prevent re-insertion of elements which have been</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><Highlight kind="comment">/// visited -- if you need to break cycles, a set will still be necessary.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="40"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="41"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The type \\c T must be default constructable to a null value that will be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00042" /><CodeLine lineNumber="42"><Highlight kind="comment">/// ignored. It is an error to insert such a value, and popping elements will</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00043" /><CodeLine lineNumber="43"><Highlight kind="comment">/// never produce such a value. It is expected to be used with common nullable</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00044" /><CodeLine lineNumber="44"><Highlight kind="comment">/// types like pointers or optionals.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00045" /><CodeLine lineNumber="45"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00046" /><CodeLine lineNumber="46"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Internally this uses a vector to store the worklist and a map to identify</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="47"><Highlight kind="comment">/// existing elements in the worklist. Both of these may be customized, but the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00048" /><CodeLine lineNumber="48"><Highlight kind="comment">/// map must support the basic DenseMap API for mapping from a T to an integer</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="49"><Highlight kind="comment">/// index into the vector.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00050" /><CodeLine lineNumber="50"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00051" /><CodeLine lineNumber="51"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A partial specialization is provided to automatically select a SmallVector</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00052" /><CodeLine lineNumber="52"><Highlight kind="comment">/// and a SmallDenseMap if custom data structures are not provided.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00054" /><CodeLine lineNumber="54"><Highlight kind="normal">          </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> MapT = DenseMap&lt;T, ptrdiff&#95;t&gt;&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
